Below is a clean summary of everything we did, followed by a clear architecture diagram that ties together Backend, System User, App, Page, and Meta APIs.

✅ What we achieved (step-by-step summary)
1️⃣ Created a Meta Business Portfolio

This is the root container

Owns:

Facebook Page

Meta App(s)

System Users

2️⃣ Created a Facebook Page

Example: Posts Dev Page

This is where content is actually published

Pages are not apps and not users

3️⃣ Created a Meta App

Final app used: Social Management App

App type / use case:

Manage everything on your Page (Pages API)

This use case is critical — without it:

❌ No page permissions

❌ No posting

❌ Token permissions list is empty

4️⃣ Created a System User

Example: Posts Dev Backend

Purpose:

Non-human backend identity

Used by servers, cron jobs, schedulers

Role:

Admin (recommended for backend)

5️⃣ Assigned relationships correctly
✔ System User → App

The app must be installed for the system user

Otherwise:
❌ “No permissions available”

✔ System User → Page

Assigned Full control on the Page

6️⃣ Generated tokens (this is where confusion usually happens)

You now understand there are two different tokens:

🔹 A. System User Token

Identity: System User

Scope: business-level

Cannot post directly

Used to:

List pages

Generate Page tokens

Business management

🔹 B. Page Access Token ✅ (this is the important one)

Identity: Page

Generated via:

GET /me/accounts


Scopes:

pages_manage_posts

pages_read_engagement

✅ This token is used to:

Post photos

Post videos

Create feed posts

7️⃣ Posting content (working)
✔ Upload photo (file)
POST /{PAGE_ID}/photos

✔ Upload photo from URL
POST /{PAGE_ID}/photos
  url=https://public-image-url.jpg


Requirements:

Public HTTPS URL

Page access token

No publish_actions (deprecated ❌)

8️⃣ Error explained: publish_actions

❌ Deprecated for years

Facebook auto-mentions it in misleading errors

Ignore it

Your correct permission is:

pages_manage_posts

🧠 Mental model (very important)

Apps don’t post. Users don’t post. System users don’t post.
👉 Pages post. Tokens just authorize.

